                  <t:desc type="foundation">Existed aready in the pre-Christian time as the religious site of South Arabian migrants; the church was founded in a later period.</t:desc>
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabr. A new large church is under construction outside of the compound of the old church, both standing on the rock outcrop 
                     (below is the river of <t:placeName type="river" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC6519Wafadabbo">Wafadabbo</t:placeName>).
                     </t:ab>
                  <t:ab type="tabot">
                     <t:measure quantity="8"/>
                     Tābots (8): <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS5684JesusCh">Jesus</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10775Trinity">Trinity</t:persName>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS6819Mary">Mary</t:persName>, unidentified marble, 
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4377Gabriel">Gabriel</t:persName>, <t:ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/CovenantMercy">Kidāna Mǝḥrat</t:ref>, <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7049Michael">Michael</t:persName>, 
                     <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10774Paraq">Ṗarāqliṭos</t:persName>. The tābot of the local <t:persName type="tabot" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10773SadeqP">Ṣādǝqān</t:persName> (Righteous Ones) was not mentioned, probably by mistake.</t:ab>
